The sugar alcohols market is segmented by type, application, and form. In terms of type, the market is further segmented into sorbitol, xylitol, erythritol, maltitol, and others. Sorbitol is a widely used sugar alcohol due to its low calorie content and sweetness. Xylitol, on the other hand, is gaining popularity in dental care products due to its ability to prevent cavities. Erythritol is a natural sugar alcohol with zero calories, making it a preferred choice in the food and beverage industry. Maltitol is commonly used as a sugar substitute in sugar-free products. The market segmentation by application includes food & beverages, pharmaceuticals, personal care & cosmetics, and others. Sugar alcohols find extensive applications in the food and beverage industry as sweetening agents and texturizers. The pharmaceutical industry utilizes sugar alcohols in various medicines and syrups. In the personal care & cosmetics sector, sugar alcohols are used in skincare products for their moisturizing properties. The form segment of the market comprises powder and liquid forms of sugar alcohols, catering to different industry requirements.

